From the Latin, getting drunk (ubria) while eating cheeze pizza (chezza) with massive amounts of beer.  The tradition was believed to have to spread across Europe during the Roman occupation by bored troops.  Eventually, this tradition made it way to the US by way of bored troops in post WWI Italy.  Pizza and Beer were the primary food source for generations of young soldiers and now has become primary source of food millions of Americans.  The usual topic of discussion was "I wonder where all the woman are?"